        <h2 id="apple-pie">Apple Pie</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 45 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 6 porsion</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
                    <td>white sugar</td>
                    <td>     1/2 cup  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>brown sugar</td>
                    <td>1/2 cup </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>water</td>
                    <td>1/4 cup </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>butter</td>
                    <td>1/2 cup </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>apples</td>
                    <td>  4</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong>Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Melt the butter in a saucepan. Stir in flour to form a paste. Add water, white sugar and brown sugar, and bring to a boil. Reduce temperature and let simmer.
</p>
<p><strong>Step2: </strong>Place the bottom crust in your pan. Fill with apples, mounded slightly. Cover with a lattice work crust. Gently pour the sugar and butter liquid over the crust. Pour slowly so that it does not run off.</p>
<p><strong>Step3: </strong>Bake 15 minutes in the preheated oven. Reduce the temperature to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Continue baking for 35 to 45 minutes, until apples are soft.</p>
        
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/12682/apple-pie-by-grandma-ople/">Some recipes websites</a></em></p>
    
